--------------------------------------------------------------------------
DISCLAIMER
no testing has been made to ensure functionality together with other footnote
packages. Footnotes produced by \footcite and similar citing commands are not
affected.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE:

Use \footnote the usual way. If a dot (.) or a comma (,) follows the footnote
like ``\footnote{some text}.'' the package will reverse the order of footnote
and punctuation character and skip the footnote back by a small space which can
be changed using a package option:
\usepackage[after-dot-space = -.08em]{fnpct}
In other cases a small space is inserted between last word and footnote.

Options are:
  after-dot-space (initially -.06em)
  after-comma-space (initially -.06em)
  after-punct-space (set both spaces)
  before-dot-space (initially -.15em)
  before-comma-space (initially -.15em)
  before-punct-space (set both spaces)
  before-footnote-space (initially .06em)
  punct-after (boolean switch; if true the dot/comma is inserted after the
    footnote instead of before)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------